===Adjective===
'''phosphorescent'''

# A property of emitting light for a period of time after the source of excitation is taken away, e.g., in electrostatic storage tubes and cathode-ray tubes.

====Etymology====
From Greek '''[[phos]]''', ''light'', + Greek '''[[phor]]''', ''bear'', + suffix from Latin '''[[-escere]]''', ''become'', + present participle suffix '''[[-ent]]''', equivalent to English ''[[-ing]]'', from Latin present participle suffix '''[[-ens]]'''

